7. The development and implementation of Defendants’ practice of refusing to

2 allow entry to asylum seekers presenting themselves at ports of entry along the Southwestern
3 border, including all communications to Defendant employees (e.g., CBP and ICE officers)
4
working near those border ports of entry that discuss this practice, including but not limited to 5

6 discussion of “metering,” numerical or space limits on asylum claims, administrative or other

7 limits on asylum claim processing, and requiring asylum seekers to return to ports of entry at a

8 later day or time.

9

